{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/muzzle_flash", "tags": "pyro"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simple Muzzle Flash"], "extent": [0, 24]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a visible blast from the the muzzle of a firearm during shooting."], "extent": [64, 145]}, {"type": "video_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [145, 153], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["Muzzle volume and ember in the viewport. Colorspace: ACES."], "extent": [213, 286]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/pyro/shelf/shelf_muzzleflash_viewport.mp4"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [286, 294], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["Muzzle volume and ember rendered with Karma. Colorspace: ACES."], "extent": [351, 429]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/pyro/shelf/shelf_muzzleflash_karma.mp4"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [429, 444], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This shelf tool sets up a simple pyro muzzle flash source, which is rasterized into a volume using ", {"type": "code", "text": ["volumerasterizeattributes1"]}, ". Additionally, the tool generates a simple spark setup coming out from the muzzle."], "extent": [444, 657]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Simple Muzzle Flash"], "extent": [657, 701], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/muzzle_flash", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/muzzle_flash"}, " ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Simple Muzzle Flash"]}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Simple FX"]}, " tab."], "extent": [701, 807]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the location of the muzzle flash in the viewport."], "extent": [807, 875]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Working with Simple Muzzle Flash"], "extent": [875, 914], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["If you have a Houdini FX License, you can dive inside the solver and edit the subnet with custom DOP forces. Otherwise, you can stay at the SOP level and use the exposed parameters on the node."], "extent": [914, 1112]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["This muzzle flash is not simulated, so it\u2019s very quick to iterate. One tip to make the volume look like fast moving gas, is to enable ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Velocity Blur"]}, " on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Volume Rasterize Attributes"]}, " node."], "extent": [1112, 1312]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The look of the muzzle flash is created using the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pyrolook"]}, " node. By enabling ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scatter"]}, " on this node, you can make the flash emit more light."], "extent": [1312, 1459]}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["Simple Muzzle Flash"], "summary": ["Creates a visible blast from the the muzzle of a firearm during shooting."]}